# Basic commands
`django-admin startproject <project>`

`python manage.py migrate`

`python manage.py runserver`

`python manage.py runserver http://192.168.1.181:8000/`

`python manage.py startapp polls`

`python manage.py makemigrations polls`

`python manage.py shell`

`python manage.py collectstatic`

`python manage.py check --deploy`

`python manage.py flush`

`python manage.py dumpdata > backup.json`

`python manage.py loaddata backup.json`


##Migrations
Run python manage.py makemigrations to create migrations for those changes

Run python manage.py migrate to apply those changes to the database.

`python manage.py squashmigrations <appname> <squashfrom> <squashto>`


#Server

##Links
[Registering a Domain Name (Digital Ocean)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zOPH54ltGLQ&ab_channel=CodingWithMitch)

[Setup Https on Digital Ocean Ubuntu Server (Nginx and Certbot)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r-ljiO_7MME&ab_channel=CodingWithMitch)

[https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-secure-nginx-with-let-s-encrypt-on-ubuntu-20-04](https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-secure-nginx-with-let-s-encrypt-on-ubuntu-20-04)

##gunicorn commands
`sudo systemctl daemon-reload`

`sudo service gunicorn restart`

`sudo systemctl status gunicorn`

`sudo systemctl start gunicorn.socket`

`sudo systemctl enable gunicorn.socket`

`sudo systemctl status gunicorn.socket`

##Updating server files
1. `sudo cp /home/bez/projects/mango/mango.nginx /etc/nginx/sites-available/mango`
2. `sudo cp gunicorn.service /etc/systemd/system/`
3. `systemctl daemon-reload`
4. `service gunicorn restart`
5. `systemctl restart nginx`
6. `sudo nginx -t`

##Install mysql
1. `source ~/.venvs/django3.8.10/bin/activate`
2. `pip install django unicorn mysqlclient`
3. `sudo apt-get install mysql-server`
4. `sudo apt-get install gcc`
5. `pip install gunicorn`
6. `sudo apt-get install libmysqlclient21`
7. `sudo apt-get install libmysqlclient21 nginx libmysqlclient-dev`
8. https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-set-up-django-with-postgres-nginx-and-gunicorn-on-ubuntu-16-04#introduction

##Add new user
1. `adduser bez`
2. `usermod -aG sudo bez`
3. `rsync --archive --chown=bez:bez ~/.ssh /home/bez`

##Install django
1. `mkdir .venv`
2. `python3 -m venv .venv`
3. Install python: https://www.python.org/downloads/
4. Install postgres:


    [https://www.postgresql.org/download/windows/](https://www.postgresql.org/download/windows/)

5. Install psycopg:

    `pip install psycopg2-binary`

6. `py -m pip install Django`
7. `py -m django --version`
8. `py -m django startproject mango`
9. `py -m pip install mysqlclient`
10. Install mysql

##pip install
`pip freeze > requirements.txt`

`pip install -r requirements.txt`

##remove migrations
`find . -path "*/migrations/*.py" -not -name "__init__.py" -delete`

`find . -path "*/migrations/*.pyc" -delete`

##SSH
1. `ssh-keygen`
2. create suh,suh.pub - pub is put on server suh is private
3. PS C:\Users\leobe>  Get-Service -Name ssh-agent | Set-Service -StartupType Manual
4. PS C:\Users\leobe> start-service ssh-agent
5. PS S:\projects\mango_official> ssh-add C:\users\leobe\suh
Enter passphrase for C:\users\leobe\suh:
Identity added: C:\users\leobe\suh (leobe@DESKTOP)
6. ssh-keygen -f "/root/.ssh/known_hosts" -R use_your_droplet_ip

##.htaccess
    AddHandler fcgid-script .fcgi
    RewriteEngine On
    RewriteCond %{HTTP_HOST} ^(.+\.|)keefrogers.com
    RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f
    RewriteRule ^(.*)$ keefrogers.fcgi/$1 [QSA,L]
    
##keefrogers.fcgi
    #!/home/keefroge/bin/python/bin/python
    import sys
    import os
    
    project_name = "mango"
    
    sys.path.insert(0, "/home/keefroge/bin/python")
    sys.path.append(os.getcwd() + "/" + project_name)
    
    os.environ["DJANGO_SETTINGS_MODULE"] = project_name + ".settings"
    
    from django.core.servers.fastcgi import runfastcgi
    runfastcgi(method="threaded", daemonize="false"

#Code signing on mac
1. Open the Keychain Access application
2. Choose menu Keychain Access -> Certificate Assistant -> Create a Certificate...
3. Choose a name for the certificate
4. Set Identity Type to Self Signed Root
5. Set Certificate Type to Code Signing and select the Let me override defaults.
6. Click several times on Continue until you get to the Specify a Location For The Certificate screen, then set Keychain to System.
7. Double click on the certificate, open Trust section, and set Code Signing to Always Trust.
8. Exit Keychain Access application.


`sudo killall taskgated`

#Time

    import time
    start = time.perf_counter()
    time.sleep(1.5)
    end = time.perf_counter()
    print(end - start)

##Timer

    import time
    
    class Timer:
        def __enter__(self):
            self.start_time = time.perf_counter()
    
        def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_value, traceback):
            elapsed_time = time.perf_counter() - self.start_time
            print(f"Elapsed time: {elapsed_time} seconds")
    
    # Example usage
    with Timer():
        # Code block to be timed
        time.sleep(2)  # Simulating some task that takes 2 seconds

#Console

##Multiple line output

    import time
    
    total_progress = 100
    
    for progress in range(total_progress + 1):
        # Calculate the percentage of progress
        percentage = progress * 100 // total_progress
    
        # Generate the loading bar strings
        bar1 = "[" + "#" * (progress // 10) + " " * ((total_progress - progress) // 10) + "]"
        bar2 = "[" + "=" * (progress // 10) + " " * ((total_progress - progress) // 10) + "]"
    
        print("\r\033[K", end="")
        print("\033[F\033[K", end="")
    
        # Display the loading bars and percentages
        print(f"\r{bar1} {percentage}%")
        print(f"\r{bar2} {percentage}%", end="")
    
        # Delay for a short duration to simulate progress
        time.sleep(0.1)
    
    # Clear the current lines
    print("\r", end="")
    print("\r", end="")
    
    # Print the final output
    print("Loading complete!")
    print("Loading complete!")

##Colors

    COLOR_RED = '\033[91m'
    COLOR_GREEN = '\033[92m'
    COLOR_YELLOW = '\033[93m'
    COLOR_BLUE = '\033[94m'
    COLOR_RESET = '\033[0m'

    import unittest
    
    import git_status as git_status
    
    class TestGitStatus(unittest.TestCase):
        def test_get_numbers(self):
            print(git_status.get_numbers("12,2-3,15,16"))
            self.assertEqual([2,3,12,15,16], list(git_status.get_numbers("12,2-3,15,16")))
            self.assertEqual([21,23], list(git_status.get_numbers("21,23")))
    
    if __name__ == '__main__':

#.vimrc
    highlight Visual cterm=reverse gui=reverse guibg=LightBlue
    
    set expandtab
    set hidden
    set number
    set path+=.,**
    set shiftwidth=4
    set tabstop=4
    set wildignore+=**/build/**
    set wildignorecase
    set wildmenu
    
    vmap <Tab> >gv
    vmap <S-Tab> <gv
    
    call plug#begin('~/.vim/plugged')
    Plug 'ctrlpvim/ctrlp.vim'
    call plug#end()

#Navigating

| command | description |
| --- | --- |
h/j/k/l | move left/down/up/right. You can also use the arrow keys, but these are closer to the rest of the keys.
w/e/b | move forward/backward by word.
0/$ | move to the beginning/end of line.
gg/G | move to the beginning/end of the file.
Ctrl-f/Ctrl-b | move forward/backward by page.
Ctrl-e/Ctrl-y | move forward/backwards by one line.
tabe | new tab
tabn/tabp | next/prev tab

#Editing

| command | description |
| --- | --- |
i | insert text before the cursor.
a | insert text after the cursor.
o/O | open a new line below/above the current line and enter insert mode.
x | delete the character under the cursor.
dw | delete the current word.
dd | delete the current line.
y | yank (copy) the current line or selected text.
p/P | paste after/before the cursor.
. | repeat the last command.
u | undo.
Ctrl-r | redo.

#Searching

| command | description |
| --- | --- |
/text | search for "text" in the file, moving forward.
?text | search for "text" in the file, moving backward.
n/N | repeat the last / or ? search, moving forward/backward.
Shift+8 | go to next occurence of highlighted work.

#Substituting

| command | description |
| --- | --- |
:s/old/new | substitute the first "old" with "new" on the current line.
:%s/old/new/g | substitute every "old" with "new" in the entire file.
:%s/old/new/gc | substitute every "old" with "new" in the entire file, with a prompt for confirmation.

#Multiple files

| command | description |
| --- | --- |
:e filename | open a file in a new buffer.
:ls | list all open buffers.
:bn/:bp | go to the next/previous buffer.
:bd | delete a buffer (close a file).
:split filename or :sp filename | open a file in a new horizontal window.
:vsplit filename or :vsp filename | open a file in a new vertical window.
Ctrl-w w/Ctrl-w h/Ctrl-w j/Ctrl-w k/Ctrl-w l | move the cursor between windows.
:Explore or :E | open the built-in file explorer.

#Miscellaneous

| command | description |
| --- | --- |
:set number | turn on line numbering.
:set nocompatible | enable enhanced Vim features.
:syntax on | turn on syntax highlighting.
:set autoindent | turn on automatic indentation.

#Selection

| command | description |
| --- | --- |
aw | a word.
iw | inner word.
as | a sentence.
is | inner sentence.
ap | a paragraph.
ip | inner paragraph.
a( or a) | a block in parentheses.
i( or i) | inner block in parentheses.
a[ or a] | a block in brackets.
i[ or i] | inner block in brackets.
a{ or a} | a block in braces.
i{ or i} | inner block in braces.
a< or a> | a block in angle brackets.
i< or i> | inner block in angle brackets.
a' | a string in single quotes.
i' | inner string in single quotes.
a" | a string in double quotes.
i" | inner string in double quotes.

##examples
`%s/\(.*\): \(.*\)/| \1 | \2 |/g`

#Replacement and Case Conversion

| command | description |
| --- | --- |
| r | To replace the character under the cursor, type r followed by the new character. |
| ~ | To swap the case (upper to lower, lower to upper) of the character under the cursor, press ~. |
| guu | Converts the current line to lowercase. |
| gUU | Converts the current line to uppercase. |
| g~~ | Inverts case of the current line. |
| guw | Converts the current word to lowercase. |
| gUw | Converts the current word to uppercase. |
| g~iw | Inverts case of the current word. |
| ggVG= | Auto-format entire file. |
| :sort | Sort selection.

#Install vim-plug
`curl -fLo ~/.vim/autoload/plug.vim --create-dirs https://raw.githubusercontent.com/junegunn/vim-plug/master/plug.vim`

#Mappings
`vmap <Tab> >gv`

`vmap <S-Tab> <gv`
